cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.RO 

The paper focuses on a computer vision task of hand parsing using a fully convolutional neural network. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel parsing framework that involves designing a Deconvolution and Bilinear Interpolation Block (DB-Block) for upsampling and merging the features of different scales, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of cs.MM (Multimedia). Additionally, the paper addresses the problem of data imbalance, which is a common problem in many computer vision tasks, indicating that it may also belong to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper's focus on hand parsing suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of cs.RO (Robotics).
